member.summary: Adds specified method to injection.
member.param: Value indicating whether existing method is overwritten.
member.exception: Thrown if specified method is null.
Thrown if specified method has no storage path or method with same storage path was already added.
member.remarks:
This function adds the specified method to the injection and performs the required linking in data model. However, the method is NOT copied to result set location. For conditional result set copy of the method use
. The business object model accepts only one data analysis method per injection (method with
= ). Therefore, when adding a data analysis method, an existing one is removed. This methods preserves existing OriginalFilePath values if they are relative. For absolute paths the value is set identical to the LinkedMethodPath property of MethodContainer (which is absolute or relative - depending on the type of DataContext).
member.returns: True if method was successfully added, false if method is already associated with injection.

member.name: M:Agilent.OpenLab.Framework.BusinessObjectModel.Injection.AddMethod(Agilent.OpenLab.Framework.BusinessObjectModel.IMethodContainer,Agilent.OpenLab.Framework.BusinessObjectModel.MethodUsageType,System.String,System.Boolean)
member.summary: Adds specified method to the injection.
member.param: The original method path (in case this method was copied into the result set from a master method). Use the absolute path to the master method.
member.exception: Thrown if specified method is null.
Thrown if specified method has no storage path or method with same storage path was already added.
member.remarks:
This function adds the specified method to the injection and performs the required linking in data model. However, the method is NOT copied to result set location. For conditional result set copy of the method use
. The business object model accepts only one data analysis method per injection (method with
= ). Therefore, when adding a data analysis method, an existing one is removed. This method sets the OriginalFilePath property of the method as a relative path to the current method root in the project. An existing OriginalFilePath value is overwritten.
member.returns: True if method was successfully added, false if method is already associated with injection.
